<item>
            <title>[QPID-863] PubSub example has a minor error in the closing logic</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-863</link>
                <project id="12310520" key="QPID">Qpid</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Listener class has the following check  - &quot;while (_finished &amp;lt; 3 &amp;amp;&amp;amp; !_failed)&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
However there are 4 topics and this loop condition causes the Listener to close after receiving 3 &quot;termination messages&quot; instead of 4.&lt;br/&gt;
Due to the volume of messages this is mostly unnoticable when run manually.&lt;br/&gt;
But this causes an intermittent failure when run with the verify scripts as due to a race condtion sometimes all messages from all 4 topics are received before close.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
